This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspect of mobile data offloading, which falls under the category of computer science networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves game theory and pricing mechanisms, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of computer science game theory (cs.GT). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant as the paper discusses the transmission of data over wireless networks. The paper also involves system and control theory (cs.SY) as it models the interactions between different participants in the offloading market. Finally, multimedia (cs.MM) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of offloading on user satisfaction.
